label: Thymine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pks at rt +1 min is in src frags of uridine

label: Uracil
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pks at rt +1 min is in src frags of uridine

label: Adenine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt +0.23 is in src frag adenosine

label: Hypoxanthine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk in pos mode at rt +1.8 min is in src frag of inosine

label: Cytosine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt +1.55 is in src frags of cytidine

label: Guanine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt +2min is in src frag of guanosine

label: Valine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt -2.5 is betaine (isomer)

label: Trehalose
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt -1.50 is sucrose (isomer)

label: Xanthine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pks at RT +7.5 and +8.5 min are in src frag of xanthosine

label: Biotin
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt +2.50 is X

label: Betaine
indentification notes: ionizes in pos polarity. HILz: pk at rt +2.5 is valine (isomer)

label: Thiamine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities.  HILz: pks at RT -5.6 and -6.6 min are X

label: Trigonelline
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: multiple pks in pos mode at rt - 0.7, - 2.0 and -3.0 are not trigonelline

label: Taurine
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk in pos mode at rt +2.25 min is not taurine

label: Myo-inositol peak 1
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt -3.7 min is in glucose (isomer)

label: Sucrose
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt +1.50 is trehalose (isomer)

label: Myo-inositol both peaks
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt -3.8 min is in glucose (isomer)

label: Myo-inositol peak 2
indentification notes: ionizes in both polarities. HILz: pk at rt -3.9 min is in glucose (isomer)
